Chocolate Distribution problem
// Java program to solve chocolate distribution
// problem using Sliding Window

import java.util.Arrays;

class GfG {

    static int findMinDiff(int[] arr, int m) {
        int n = arr.length;

        // Sort the given packets
        Arrays.sort(arr);

        int minDiff = Integer.MAX_VALUE;

        for (int i = 0; i + m - 1 < n; i++) {

            // calculate difference of current window
            int diff = arr[i + m - 1] - arr[i];

            // if current difference is smaller
            // then update the minimum difference
            if (diff < minDiff)
                minDiff = diff;
        }
        return minDiff;
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int[] arr = {7, 3, 2, 4, 9, 12, 56};
        int m = 3;

        System.out.println(findMinDiff(arr, m));
    }
}
pattern used 
The idea is to first sort the array, then use sliding window technique to choose consecutive elements to 
minimize the difference. After sorting the array, the difference between the maximum and minimum values in any window of size m is minimized. 
